k" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$60</span> from <span>We Love Jam</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>A sure way to delight the toast-loving MIL in your life is to send a <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/42788/168260/4/160315/?merchant=We%20Love%20Jam" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="We Love Jam" data-pick-type-id="7" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/42788/168260/4/160315/?merchant=We%20Love%20Jam" data-vars-store="We Love Jam" data-gtm-context="chapter_delectable-jam" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="We Love Jam" data-pid="42788" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/42788/168260/4/160315/?merchant=We%20Love%20Jam">pretty gift box with six jars of jam</a> and a personal note. One of our <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/gifts/best-gift-baskets/#sweet-gift-baskets">favorite gift baskets</a> comes from Welovejam, a two-person company in Santa Clara, California, that uses only locally grown fruit. Choose from flavors like blackberry vanilla, apricot bing cherry, or tangy mango lime. The available flavors change seasonally—you write your choices in a pleasingly analog text box on the site—but the deliciousness stays the same. Whatever flavors your recipient is blessed with (Welovejam has a four-jar option, too), you can be sure the jam will be spreadable, fresh, and way better than the grocery store options.</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="b6d81848 d47f7b03" id="a-beautiful-watering-system" expanded=""><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0 e5f9b502"><h2 class="e823fba7" aria-controls="a-beautiful-watering-system-panel" aria-selected="true" role="tab" tabindex="0" data-gtm-element="chapter_heading" data-gtm-trigger="single_chapter" data-chapter-name="A beautiful watering system" data-expand-close="close" data-chapter-index="14">A beautiful watering system</h2></div></div><div id="a-beautiful-watering-system-panel" class="fa265be5" aria-labelledby="a-beautiful-watering-system" aria-hidden="false" role="tabpanel"><div class=" chapter__content-wrapper"><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><figure id="attachment_376707" class="wp-caption alignnone"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image"><img loading="lazy" alt="Brass Plant Straws in two large potted plants." src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=265" data-src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=570" data-srcset="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=570 768w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=570&amp;dpr=1.5 1152w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=570&amp;dpr=2 1536w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=530 585w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=530&amp;dpr=1.5 877w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=530&amp;dpr=2 1170w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=425 480w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2024/04/mother-in-law-2048px-3552.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=425&amp;dpr