45</span> from <span>Amazon</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>This <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46723/197420/4/152174/?merchant=Amazon" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-pick-type-id="7" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46723/197420/4/152174/?merchant=Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-gtm-context="chapter_piscine-pottery" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Amazon" data-pid="46723" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/46723/197420/4/152174/?merchant=Amazon">fish-shaped pitcher</a> is so darn cute and versatile it will please just about anyone. Made of durable stoneware and available in a kaleidoscope of different colors to suit any home, this 42-ounce vessel makes a <a href="http://www.gurglepot.com/Assets/gurgle.wav" rel="noopener" target="_blank">soft gurgling sound</a>—not unlike a babbling brook—as it pours, which is both charming and silly. It functions equally well as a pitcher for lemonade or a vase for flowers.</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="b6d81848 d47f7b03" id="the-softest-blanket" expanded=""><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0 e5f9b502"><h2 class="e823fba7" aria-controls="the-softest-blanket-panel" aria-selected="true" role="tab" tabindex="0" data-gtm-element="chapter_heading" data-gtm-trigger="single_chapter" data-chapter-name="The softest blanket" data-expand-close="close" data-chapter-index="24">The softest blanket</h2></div></div><div id="the-softest-blanket-panel" class="fa265be5" aria-labelledby="the-softest-blanket" aria-hidden="false" role="tabpanel"><div class=" chapter__content-wrapper"><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><figure id="attachment_