b787"><div><h3 class="b550f131 e26624a1 a1a87f29"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28949/148737/4/173597?merchant=Zingerman&#x27;s" class="dfb6b88d" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Zingerman’s The Weekender Gift Box" data-gtm-element="callout_product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-pick-type-id="7" data-pid="28949" data-store="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-vars-store="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28949/148737/4/173597?merchant=Zingerman&#x27;s" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_name" data-scp="callout_product" data-gtm-context="inline">Zingerman’s The Weekender Gift Box</a></h3><h2 class="eafb159a"></h2></div><p class="ec57f3ca" data-scp="callout_description">This ample gift box provides sweet and salty sustenance, but the coffee cake takes the prize.</p><div class="dded66b7"><div data-scp="removed"><h4 class="efa3259d">Buying Options</h4><div class="b279b202 product-pricebox-0" data-source-id-order="0" data-country-code="US"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28949/148737/4/173597?merchant=Zingerman&#x27;s" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-pick-type-id="7" data-pid="28949" data-store="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-vars-store="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28949/148737/4/173597?merchant=Zingerman&#x27;s" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$110</span> from <span>Zingerman&#x27;s</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>For a genuinely good variety of sweet and savory treats, give your mother-in-law the <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28949/148737/4/111424/?merchant=Zingerman&#x27;s" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-pick-type-id="7" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28949/148737/4/111424/?merchant=Zingerman&#x27;s" data-vars-store="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-gtm-context="chapter_a-basket-of-treats" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Zingerman&#x27;s" data-pid="28949" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/28949/148737/4/111424/?merchant=Zingerman&#x27;s">Zingerman’s Weekender Gift Box</a>, one of <a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/gifts/gift-baskets-that-dont-suck/">our favorite gift baskets</a>. Inside are two rich brownies, salty salami and cheese, a whole loaf of bread, and crunchy peanut brittle. The sour cream coffee cake is particularly transcendent: Tender, walnut-and-cinnamon-studded cake sits beneath a slightly crunchy crust. Staffers say it actually gets better as the days go by—if it lasts that long, that is.</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="b6d81848 d47f7b03" id="gateway-to-the-outdoors" expanded=""><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0 e5f9b502"><h2 class="e823fba7" aria-controls="gateway-to-the-outdoors-panel" aria-selected="true" role="tab" tabindex="0" data-gtm-element="chapter_heading" data-gtm-trigger="single_chapter" data-chapter-name="Gateway to the outdoors" data-expand-close="close" data-chapter-index="26">Gateway to the outdoors</h2></div></div><div id="gateway-to-the-outdoors-panel" class="fa265be5" aria-labelledby="gateway-to-the-outdoors" aria-hidden="false" role="tabpanel"><div class=" chapter__content-wrapper"><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><figure id="attachment_308156" class="wp-caption alignnone"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image"><img loading="lazy" alt="Two bikers on a trail overlooking a National park." src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=265" data-src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=570" data-srcset="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=570 768w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=570&amp;dpr=1.5 1152w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=570&amp;dpr=2 1536w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=530 585w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=530&amp;dpr=1.5 877w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=530&amp;dpr=2 1170w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=425 480w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=425&amp;dpr=1.5 720w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=425&amp;dpr=2 960w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=265 320w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=265&amp;dpr=1.5 480w,https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/04/gifts-for-mother-in-law-2048px-1326653507.jpg?auto=webp&amp;quality=60&amp;width=265&amp;dpr=2 640w" width="570" height="380" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce alignnone size-large wp-image-308156"/></div><figcaption class="wp-caption-text"> <!-- --> <span class="wp-caption-text wp-caption-credit">Photo: David Rodríguez Sánchez/iStock</span></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><div class="ebb615ab global-cob e1e566ad" data-scp="callout"><div id="callout-chapter-7-22" class="fd1ac384" data-scp="callout_item" data-testid="callout" data-pid="29433"><span class="ddf294c5"><div class="fabe3ad3"><div class="e14704b2" role="button" tabindex="0" data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="29433"><span aria-label="Save Product" class="a478f5d2  " data-gtm-trigger="save_product" data-save-content-value="true" data-save-content-id="29433"></span></div></div></span><div class="f1cabe17"><div class="f31f6df1"><div class="efc734d0 eae76d54"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/173598?merchant=REI" class="fa8c1483 product-merchant-link-button" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-store="REI" data-vars-store="REI" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/173598?merchant=REI" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_image" data-scp="removed" tabindex="-1" data-pid="29433" data-gtm-context="inline"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image"><img alt="" itemProp="image" data-src="https://d1b5h9psu9yexj.cloudfront.net/29433/America-the-Beautiful--The-National-Parks-and-Federal-Recreational-Lands-Pass_20230417-152926_full.jpeg" width="570" height="380" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce" loading="lazy"/></div></a></div><div class="ce2bb787"><div><h3 class="b550f131 e26624a1 a1a87f29"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/173598?merchant=REI" class="dfb6b88d" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="The National Parks and Federal Recreational Lands Annual Pass" data-gtm-element="callout_product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="REI" data-pick-type-id="7" data-pid="29433" data-store="REI" data-vars-store="REI" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/173598?merchant=REI" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_name" data-scp="callout_product" data-gtm-context="inline">The National Parks and Federal Recreational Lands Annual Pass</a></h3><h2 class="eafb159a"></h2></div><p class="ec57f3ca" data-scp="callout_description">Not all national parks have entry fees. But 109 of the top ones do, and outdoor enthusiasts will appreciate this pass, which waives the $10 to $20 per-park charges for an entire calendar year.</p><div class="dded66b7"><div data-scp="removed"><h4 class="efa3259d">Buying Options</h4><div class="b279b202 product-pricebox-0" data-source-id-order="0" data-country-code="US"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/173598?merchant=REI" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="REI" data-pick-type-id="7" data-pid="29433" data-store="REI" data-vars-store="REI" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/173598?merchant=REI" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$80</span> from <span>REI</span></a></div><div class="b279b202 product-pricebox-1" data-source-id-order="1" data-country-code="US"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/149407/4/173598?merchant=USGS%20Store" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="USGS Store" data-pick-type-id="7" data-pid="29433" data-store="USGS Store" data-vars-store="USGS Store" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/149407/4/173598?merchant=USGS%20Store" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$80</span> from <span>USGS Store</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>You may not agree with your mother-in-law about everything, but about this you certainly shall: National parks are awesome. Whether your MIL is a serious hiker or someone who’d prefer to experience Yosemite Valley from the comfort of a car, this <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/111425/?merchant=REI" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="REI" data-pick-type-id="7" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/111425/?merchant=REI" data-vars-store="REI" data-gtm-context="chapter_gateway-to-the-outdoors" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="REI" data-pid="29433" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29433/194806/4/111425/?merchant=REI">pass</a> will offer her (and three guests) access to any and all national parks in the United States for one year. Plan this gift in advance, though—shipping on standard passes can take over a week, and the lifetime <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/50478/180504/4/145146/?merchant=USGS%20Store" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="USGS Store" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/50478/180504/4/145146/?merchant=USGS%20Store" data-vars-store="USGS Store" data-gtm-context="chapter_gateway-to-the-outdoors" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="USGS Store" data-pid="50478" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/50478/180504/4/145146/?merchant=USGS%20Store">Senior Pass</a> (available to residents age 62 and over) can take even longer. Luckily, both are available for immediate pickup at <a href="https://www.nps.gov/planyourvisit/pickup-pass-locations.htm" rel="noopener" target="_blank">several distribution sites</a>.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><div class="ff31b4af" data-ad-element="outer_ad_container" data-scp="removed"><div class="e5d43c70"><p class="cca4d3b6">Advertisement</p><a href="#after-dfp-ad-chapter-mid-15" class="css-777zgl">SKIP ADVERTISEMENT</a><div class="ad dfp-ad-chapter-mid-15-wrapper css-rfqw0c" id="dfp-ad-chapter-mid-15"></div><div id="after-dfp-ad-chapter-mid-15"></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section><section class="b6d81848 d47f7b03" id="a-breezy-apron" expanded=""><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0 e5f9b502"><h2 class="e823fba7" aria-controls="a-breezy-apron-panel" aria-selected="true" role="tab" tabindex="0" data-gtm-element="chapter_heading" data-gtm-trigger="single_chapter" data-chapter-name="A breezy apron" data-expand-close="close" data-chapter-index="27">A breezy apron</h2></div></div><div id="a-breezy-apron-panel" class="fa265be5" aria-labelledby="a-breezy-apron" aria-hidden="false" role="tabpanel"><div class=" chapter__content-wrapper"><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><figure id="attachment_342996" class="wp-caption alignnone"><div class="ec5f8867 global_chapter__arp_image" style="padding-bottom:66.70%;display:inline"><img alt="A person wearing the Rough Linen Bella Pinafore Apron" data-src="https://cdn.thewirecutter.com/wp-content/media/2023/10/aprons-2048px-0602.jpg?auto=webp&amp;width=1024" width="1024" height="683" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce alignnone size-large wp-image-342996" loading="lazy"/></div><figcaption class="wp-caption-text"> <!-- --> <span class="wp-caption-text wp-caption-