_image"><img alt="" itemProp="image" data-src="https://d1b5h9psu9yexj.cloudfront.net/29703/Jono-Pandolfi-Oval-Platter_20220928-132415_full.jpeg" width="570" height="380" class="cf3feb4c c882c9ce" loading="lazy"/></div></a></div><div class="ce2bb787"><div><h3 class="b550f131 e26624a1 a1a87f29"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29703/149747/4/173604?merchant=Jono%20Pandolfi" class="dfb6b88d" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" title="Jono Pandolfi Medium Oval Platter" data-gtm-element="callout_product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Jono Pandolfi" data-pick-type-id="7" data-pid="29703" data-store="Jono Pandolfi" data-vars-store="Jono Pandolfi" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29703/149747/4/173604?merchant=Jono%20Pandolfi" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_name" data-scp="callout_product" data-gtm-context="inline">Jono Pandolfi Medium Oval Platter</a></h3><h2 class="eafb159a"></h2></div><p class="ec57f3ca" data-scp="callout_description">This lovely 8-by-12-inch stoneware platter is a particularly handy size, ideal for family-style entrees, cheese plates, or pastry spreads. Plus, it’s microwave- and dishwasher-safe.</p><div class="dded66b7"><div data-scp="removed"><h4 class="efa3259d">Buying Options</h4><div class="b279b202 product-pricebox-0" data-source-id-order="0" data-country-code="US"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29703/149747/4/173604?merchant=Jono%20Pandolfi" class="b50e01ee" data-gtm-element="callout_buy_button_impression" data-link-type="button" data-merchant="Jono Pandolfi" data-pick-type-id="7" data-pid="29703" data-store="Jono Pandolfi" data-vars-store="Jono Pandolfi" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29703/149747/4/173604?merchant=Jono%20Pandolfi" rel="sponsored noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-context="inline" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_button"><span>$68</span> from <span>Jono Pandolfi</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p>This <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29703/149747/4/114035/?merchant=Jono%20Pandolfi" rel="noopener sponsored" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Jono Pandolfi" data-pick-type-id="7" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29703/149747/4/114035/?merchant=Jono%20Pandolfi" data-vars-store="Jono Pandolfi" data-gtm-context="chapter_a-chic-durable-platter" data-gtm-element="product_link_impression" data-link-type="link" data-merchant="Jono Pandolfi" data-pid="29703" data-url="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/29703/149747/4/114035/?merchant=Jono%20Pandolfi">oval serving platter</a>—made by New Jersey–based artisan Jono Pandolfi—comes recommended by senior editor Marguerite Preston, who uses it regularly in her own home when she hosts dinner parties. “The modern, minimalist shape will look good in just about any setting,” she says, “and this platter can function equally well for presenting a roast chicken or a cheese plate.” Pandolfi sells a lot of his stoneware to eateries (including Jean-Georges Restaurants). The stylish pieces are durable as well as microwave- and dishwasher-safe.</p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p><strong><em>We love finding gifts that are unusual, thoughtful, and well vetted. See even </em><em><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/gifts/">more gift ideas we recommend</a></em><em>.</em></strong></p></div></div></div><div><div class="a1497183"><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0"><p><em>Mari Uyehara contributed reporting. This article was edited by Hannah Morrill and Jennifer Hunter. </em></p></div></div></div></div></div></section></div><div class="f21e64f1 b5823c44 cdde21c0 e5f9b502 d4b00d15"><div data-scp="removed"><a id="author-bios"></a><h2 cla